### Section 7: Rules of Engagement

**Production environment:** Assessor has read-only IAM access to the production AWS account. No write actions, no resource modifications, no active exploitation. All AWS console review activities are logged in CloudTrail — assessor acknowledges that their activities will appear in the audit trail.

**Test environment:** Assessor has standard user access to the OpenMRS test environment for application testing. Test environment contains synthetic data only — no real patient records. Assessor acknowledges the prohibition on introducing test data to the production environment.

**No active exploitation:** The assessment includes testing whether controls are implemented and effective, not penetration testing to exploit vulnerabilities. Finding that MFA can be bypassed is a finding; demonstrating lateral movement through the account after bypassing MFA is out of scope.

**Communication:** All findings are communicated first to the ISSO during the preliminary findings meeting, then formally in the SAR. The assessor does not communicate findings directly to the AO without the ISSO's knowledge.

**Incident handling:** If the assessor discovers evidence of an active security incident (unauthorized access, active malware, data exfiltration in progress), they notify the ISSO immediately and follow MyClinic's incident response plan. Assessment activities are suspended until the incident is resolved.

**Data handling:** The assessor treats all system documentation, configuration data, and evidence as confidential. All materials are handled per the NDA executed before engagement began. Assessment work product is retained by the firm for one year and then securely destroyed per the firm's retention policy.

