### Section 8: Assessment Deliverables

**Security Assessment Report (SAR):**
- Executive summary suitable for AO review
- Control-by-control findings organized by control family
- Finding severity ratings: High (immediate remediation required before ATO), Moderate (remediation required — POA&M), Low (remediation recommended — POA&M or accepted risk)
- Root cause analysis for each finding
- Specific remediation recommendations
- Summary of POA&M items reviewed — status confirmed or discrepancy noted
- Assessment limitations (any controls not fully assessed and why)

**Evidence documentation:**
- Annotated evidence package referencing specific documents reviewed and test results
- Test execution records with screenshots for all test procedures
- Interview notes (summary form — not verbatim transcripts)

**Delivery timeline:** SAR draft delivered 4 business days after assessment completion; final SAR delivered 3 business days after ISSO factual accuracy review.

